# 4. 憂いの道中

Shizuku: Thank goodness we made it here on time.
Shiho: On time? We're not supposed to meet for another thirty minutes...
Shiho: We didn't have to rush out of the house like that.
Shizuku: I know... But what if Tsukasa and Saki also got here early out of sheer excitement?
Shiho: Yeah, I don't think...
???: Hey, Shiho! Shizuku!
Tsukasa: Good morning to the both of you! Wonderful weather for a day trip, wouldn't you say?!
Shiho: They're really here...
Shizuku: Good morning. I had a feeling that you two wouldn't be far behind us.
Saki: Hehe. We ended up getting everything ready way before when we originally planned on leaving!
Saki: We were both so excited that we decided to come here early!
Shizuku: That's perfectly understandable. I was also so excited that I kept walking between my room and the front entrance.
Shiho: You all sound like elementary schoolers who can't wait to go on a field trip...
Tsukasa: Anyway, I'm glad we're all here. Let's have as much fun as we can today!
Saki & Shizuku: Yeah!
Shiho: Anyway, let's start making our way towards the station.
Shizuku: Okay!
Saki: Oh, can we stop by the vending machines first? I forgot to buy a drink...
Tsukasa: Our train isn't scheduled to depart for a little while, so you should have plenty of time. Just be careful!
Saki: Okay! Then, I'll be right back!
Shizuku: Actually, I might join you...
Shizuku: Umm... Saki went that way, yes?
Shiho: Okay, see you in...
Shiho: No, Shizuku, wait!
Tsukasa: Not good! She's sure to get lost! We need to chase after her, Shiho...!
Saki: A trip like this means...snacks!
Saki: So, everyone, let's break out...! The potato chips♪
Shiho: I knew you'd bring some.
Saki: Yeah, because they're yummy. And I love the texture!
Saki: I even have some mini-star ramen for you, Shiho♪
Shiho: Wait, you bought some just for me? Thanks...
Shizuku: Come to think of it, Shii, you've loved these ever since you were little.
Tsukasa: I'm also a longtime fan. Particularly because it has “star” in its name! I remember a time when I had these every day!
Shiho: I'd rather not be seen as that big a fanatic.
Saki: Haha♪ Anyway, I'll open these up!
Saki: Huh? Whoa...!
Shizuku: Oh, it's all over the floor now.
Tsukasa: H-Hurry, we need to clean this up! Before we arrive at the next station!
Saki: Oh, I'm so sorry...!
Shiho: Oh, the next station's our stop. Start packing, you guys.
Saki: Okay!
Tsukasa: Hmm... Hm...?
Shizuku: Is something the matter, Tsukasa?
Tsukasa: Where... Where is it...?!
Tsukasa: Has anyone seen my ticket?!
Saki: Wait, don't tell me you lost it!
Tsukasa: I've checked all my pockets, bag and everywhere else! It's completely vanished! There's no way they're going to let me out of the station!
Shiho: I mean, why didn't you just use your smart card?
Tsukasa: The answer to that is simple! A physical ticket adds to the sentimental value of this trip!
Shiho: Okay...?
Shizuku: That reminds me... Didn't you put it in your wallet because you were worried that you'd lose it if you put it in one of your pockets?
Tsukasa: Oh...
Tsukasa: O-Of coooooourse!
Tsukasa: Alright, we're here!
Saki: *Stretch* The air here feels so fresh and clean.
Shizuku: And the village has such a wonderful atmosphere to it. I'm very much looking forward to exploring it.
Shiho: *Sigh* (We finally made it...)
Shiho: (Our trip's just begun, but I'm already exhausted.)
Saki: Hey, check it out! They've got one of those stand-in boards! Let's take a group photo!
Tsukasa: Oh, what a colorful cast of characters! Alright, I'll be... This octopus at the top!
Shizuku: Then, I'll be the tanuki.
Saki: Let's go, Shiho! Hurry!
Shiho: This only has room for three people, so I'll be the photographer for this one.
Shizuku: Oh, you're right. I wish we could all be in it together...
Tsukasa: Then, why don't we switch once you've taken ours? I'll take over on the camera next, Shiho!
Saki: Oh, Tsukasa, nice idea!
Shiho: No, we don't need to take that many...
Shiho: (Geez, these three really just do whatever they feel... They're the complete opposite of me. I have no way of predicting what they're gonna do next...)
Shiho: (I can't let my guard down.)
